<paragraph id="8628475BFFB18502FF13F9B9FDFFF936" blockId="22.[136,1452,1571,1706]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FF13F9B9FEE9F9FD" bold="true" box="[189,294,1607,1633]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB18502FE88F9B9FDA6F9FD" authorityName="Frey &amp; Sanson" authorityYear="2006" box="[294,617,1607,1633]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conceicionensis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FE88F9B9FDA6F9FD" box="[294,617,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Myoxanthus conceicionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB18502FC04F9B9FC3DF9FD" box="[938,1010,1607,1633]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB18502FB44F9B6FAB0F9FD" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1258,1407,1608,1633]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FB44F9B6FAB0F9FD" box="[1258,1407,1608,1633]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">M. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but easily distinguished from the latter by purplish flowers 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FD5DF992FCC5F919" box="[755,778,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. yellowish to brownish and purple stripped sepals 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FAECF992FA96F919" box="[1346,1369,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. sepals with circular purple to dark red warts.
</paragraph>
